<div type="definition">
<p>PLACE UNDER the SKY.</p>
<p>[[WELT]]</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria" resp="#CH" modified="2023-08-02T21:22:04.253+09:00">
            <p>1. The current term for the inhabited sublunar world on earth (often particularly that part of it which is populated or at least dominated by the Han/華夏 people) is tiān xià 天下 "All under Heaven". Compare the Greek oikoumenē.</p>
            <p>2. Hǎi nèi 海內 refers to what is surrounded by the four seas, i.e. the whole of the land mass of the world.</p>
            <p>3. Sì hǎi 四海 "the Four Seas" includes the landmass between these Four Seas. (The names of these Four Seas are not entirely clear. Perhaps the Eastern, Southern, Northern and Western Seas.)</p>
            <p>4. Liù hé 六合 refers to everything in all dimensiones east, west, south, north, below, above.</p>
            <p>5. Shì 世 sometimes refers to the world as it is now, the world one lives in.</p>
            <p>6. Jiǔ zhōu 九州 refers to the nine regions of the world.</p>
        </div>
